Package hu.bme.mit.theta.core.type.abstracttype

package hu.bme.mit.theta.core.type.abstracttype
Expressions that work with multiple types. Use AbstractExprs to create them. Note that these are abstract classes, and the corresponding expression for a given type will be created (e.g., integer addition).

Arithmetic: - AddExpr: addition - DivExpr: division - MulExpr: multiplication - SubExpr: subtraction

Comparison: - EqExpr: equal - GeqExpr: greater or equal - GtExpr: greater - LeqExpr: less or equal - LtExpr: less - NeqExpr: not equal

Other - CastExpr: cast
